#ident	"@(#)proto:desktop/menus/fd/unexpdisk2	1.1"

# This file is appended to error.1 to make an error screen
.ur
ERROR: Fatal Error On Second Hard Disk
.helpbanner
Help: Fatal Error On Second Hard Disk
.top

An error occurred while attempting to write data to the second hard disk.
The UNIX System Installation cannot continue.

After you press 'ENTER' the system will be shut down.  If you wish to retry
installing the UNIX System, put the Boot Diskette 1 of 3 in the boot
floppy drive and reboot your computer.
.help
For detailed instructions, press the 'F1' (or '?') key at any time.

An error occurred while attempting to write data to the second hard disk.
The UNIX System Installation cannot continue.

Your options include:

-- retry installation of the UNIX System. Changing the location of the
UNIX System partition on the hard disk may solve the problem.

-- run diagnostic programs supplied by your computer vendor to determine
the cause of the problem.

-- contact the customer support of your computer vendor

Refer to the "Troubleshooting" section of the Installation Guide for
more information.
